span=\"2\" | ''Teddy Riley, the First Expansion In Asia''\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | \"Masquerade\" (\uac00\uba74\ubb34\ub3c4\ud68c)\n| 192 || \u2014\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | \"Pop Pop Pop\"\n| 66 || \u2014\n|''Time to Rock da Show''\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | \"Style\" \n| 2012\n| 40 || 47\n| rowspan=\"2\" | ''Just Go (Goodbye's the New Hello)''\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | \"Just Go\"\n| 2013\n| 26 || 34\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Demonstrate\"\n| 2015\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n| ''Demonstrate''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Start a Fire\"\n| 2016\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n| rowspan=\"2\" | ''Start a Fire''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Make Me Ah\"\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2017\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Beep Beep Beep\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n| rowspan=\"2\" | ''Refresh 7th''\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | \"Breathe Heavy\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n|- \n| colspan=\"7\" style=\"font-size:8pt;\" | \"\u2014\" denotes releases that did not chart or were not released in that region.\n|}\n\n==Videography==\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2011\n| \"Dr. Feel Good\"\n|-\n| \"Dr. Feel Good\" <small>(Uncut English version)</small>\n|-\n| \"Pop Pop Pop\"\n|-\n| 2012\n| \"Style\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2013\n| \"Just Go\"\n|-\n| \"Up\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2015\n| \"Demonstrate\"\n|-\n| \"Demonstrate\" <small>(Modified version with Alex)</small>\n|-\n| 2016\n| \"Start a Fire\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2017\n| \"Beep Beep Beep\" <small>(Dance version)</small>\n|-\n| \"Breathe Heavy\" <small>(Special performance video)</small>\n|-\n| \"Breathe Heavy\" <small>(Dance version)</small>\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist-ua}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Rania (band)}}\n*[http://cafe.daum.net/1248./ Official fancafe]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:K-pop music groups]]\n[[Category:South Korean dance music groups]]\n[[Category:South Korean girl groups]]\n[[Category:2011 establishments in South Korea]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|South Korean girl group}} \n{{unreliable sources|date=December 2014|reason=Websites like Allkpop are not reliable sources}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2018}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Rania\n| background       = group_or_band\n| image            = 170915 KBS \ubba4\uc9c1\ubc45\ud06c \ucd9c\uadfc\uae38 BP \ub77c\ub2c8\uc544 01.jpg\n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = yes\n| caption          = Refresh 7th line-up.\n| alias            = BP Rania (2016\u20132018)\n| origin           = South Korea\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[Synthpop|synthpop]]|[[Dancehall|dancehall]]}}\n| years_active     = 2011\u20132018\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n* [[DR Music]]\n}}\n| website          = {{url|http://cafe.daum.net/1248./}}\n| current_members  = * Hyeme\n* Youngheun\n* Seunghyun\n*Larissa\n| Former_members   = *Yijo\n*Joy\n*Riko\n*Jooyi\n*Di\n*T-ae\n*Xia\n*Yina\n*[[Alexandra Reid|Alex]]\n*Yumin\n*Ttabo\n*Zi.U\n*Jieun\n* Namfon\n}}\n\n'''Rania''' ({{Korean|\ub77c\ub2c8\uc544}}; shortened from \"Regeneration Idol of Asia\"), formerly known as '''BP Rania''' (shortened from \"Black Pearl Rania\") is a South Korean [[girl group]] formed by [[DR Music]] in 2011, created by American [[Teddy Riley]].<ref name=\"both\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/2011/04/new-group-rania-dreams-to-conquer-korea-and-america|title=New group Rania dreams to conquer Korea and America|work=Allkpop|date=6 April 2011}}</ref> They debuted as Rania with their debut single album ''Teddy Riley, The First Expansion In Asia'' with title track \"Dr Feel Good\" released in April 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?sm=tab_txc&where=people_profile&ie=utf8&query=%EB%9D%BC%EB%8B%88%EC%95%84&os=506442|script-title=ko:\ub77c\ub2c8\uc544 :: \ub124\uc774\ubc84 \ud1b5\ud569\uac80\uc0c9|work=Naver|accessdate=13 October 2011|language=Korean}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n===Pre-debut===\nRania was originally set to debut in mid 2010 as the third generation of [[Baby V.O.X.]], however their record company [[DR Music]] decided to rebrand them as a new group named Rania with eight members: Saem (later known as Yina), Lucy (later known as Jooyi), Riko, Joy, Di, T-ae, Xia and Sarah.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/2010/07/rookie-girl-group-rania-to-debut-in-august |title=Rookie girl group Rania to debut in August|publisher=Allkpop.com|date=25 July 2010|accessdate=29 June 2012}}</ref> T-ae, Riko and Yina were chosen to star alongside former [[2PM]] member [[Jay Park]] in his movie Hype Nation,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hankyung.com/news/app/newsview.php?aid=201006153533k|title=\uadf8\ub8f9 \ub77c\ub2c8\uc544\uc758 \ud2f0\uc560, \ubc15\uc7ac\ubc94\uacfc '\ud558\uc774\ud504\ub124\uc774\uc158' \ucd9c\uc5f0 \ud655\uc815|date=15 June 2010|language=Korean|website=[[Korea Economic Daily]]|trans-title=Rania's T-ae and Jay Park confirmed to appear in 'Hype Nation'}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Rookie girl group Rania reveals their leader|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2010/07/rookie-girl-group-rania-reveals-their-leader|date=26 July 2010}}</ref> causing DR Music to push back the group's debut. At the beginning of 2011, Sarah Wang made her decision to leave the group and was replaced by [[Chinese people|Chinese]] trainee Yijo. Before the addition of Yijo, Thai Korean trainee Data (Song Daeun) and Canadian Korean trainee Minhee (Moon Minhee) were set to take Sarah's place. However, Minhee left due to parental disapproval due to her age (at the time she was 15), and Data left due to homesickness (her family resided in Thailand).\n\n===2011\u20132012: Debut and line-up changes===\n[[File:Rania at the Multicultural Festival, Gyeonggi-do, September 2011 01.jpg|thumb|left|Rania on stage at the Multicultural Festival in Gyeonggi-do, in September 2011.]]\nRania made their debut in April 2011<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/2011/03/rookie-group-rania-to-have-debut-showcase-on-april-6th|title=Rookie group 'Rania' to hold debut showcase on April 6th |publisher=Allkpop.com|date=30 March 2011 |accessdate=29 June 2012}}</ref> as an eight-member group, consisting of Saem, Jooyi, Riko, Joy, Di, T-ae, Xia and Yijo. However, upon their debut EP's release, Yijo was not present for live performances. It was later revealed that Yijo was having issues with her work visa. She left the group shortly after.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/2011/04/rania-releases-debut-single-dr-feel-good|title=[Update: MV&#93; Rania releases debut single, \"Dr Feel Good\"|publisher=Allkpop.com|date=5 April 2011|accessdate=29 June 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"yijo\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2011/04/rania-adds-new-member-lee-jo-releases-new-version-of-dr-feel-good|title=Rania adds new member Lee Jo & releases new version of \"Dr Feel Good\"|date=17 April 2011}}</ref> On April 6 they performed on [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]]' ''[[Music Bank (TV series)|Music Bank]]'', with the title track \"Dr Feel Good\", composed by producer [[Teddy Riley]]. The song was originally given to [[Lady Gaga]].<ref name=\"gaga\">{{cite web|url=http://biz.heraldcorp.com/common_prog/newsprint.php?ud=20100927000079|title=\uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 '\ub77c\ub2c8\uc544' \uad6d\ub0b4 \ucd5c\ucd08\ub85c \ud55c\u318d\ubbf8 \ub3d9\uc2dc \ub370\ubdd4|trans-title=Upcoming girl group Rania to debut in both America and Korea|website=Heraldcorp.com|date=27 September 2010|accessdate=28 March 2015|language=Korean}}</ref> However, since their music video and live performances caused controversy in Korea as some viewers felt that their image and concept were too provocative,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2011040717055349312|language=Korean|title=\ubca0\uc77c\ubc97\uc740 \ub77c\ub2c8\uc544, \ud30c\uaca9\uc758\uc0c1+\uc139\uc2dc\uc548\ubb34\u00b7\u00b7'\ucda9\uaca9\uc801 \ube44\uc8fc\uc5bc'|website=Asiae.co.kr|date=7 April 2011|trans-title=Rania's cheap outfits and sexy choreography are... \"a schocking visual\"}}</ref> Rania were forced to change their choreography and make minor changes to the outfits.<ref>{{cite web|language=Korean|url=http://www.yonhapnews.co.kr/bulletin/2011/04/12/0200000000AKR20110412216700005.HTML|title=\ud3ec\ubbf8\ub2db.\ub77c\ub2c8\uc544 \"\uc120\uc815\uc801 \uc548\ubb34\uc640 \uc758\uc0c1 \uc218\uc815\"|trans-title=4Minute and Rania to make changes to their choreography and outfits|website=Yonhap News|date=12 April 2011|accessdate=28 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/2011/04/rania-revamps-choreography-and-outfits-adds-a-25-second-high-note-part|title=Rania revamps choreography and outfits, adds a 25-second high note part|work=Allkpop|date=15 April 2011}}</ref> After the conclusion of \"Dr Feel Good\" promotions, the group returned in June with their first digital single \"Masquerade\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/2011/06/rania-to-return-with-masquerade-for-follow-up-promotions|title=Rania to return with 'Masquerade' for follow-up promotions|work=Allkpop|date=4 June 2011}}</ref> (also composed by Riley).<ref name=\"gaga\"/> Despite having planned an American debut,<ref name=\"gaga\"/> the group made no advancements.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2011/05/rania-unleashes-plans-for-u-s-and-asian-advancement|title=Rania unleashes plans for U.S. and Asian advancement|date=3 May 2011}}</ref> Shortly afterwards Riley announced that he would have nothing more to do with the group after falling out with their record label, releasing a statement saying \"I wish them the best. It's not the girls I dislike, I love Rania, they would be better with me at SM Entertainment. Their manager does shady business, used me for my music. I love Rania, I just don't like their company business. That's why they are not getting bigger. They don't do business upfront. They used my name every where then back door me on the group. It's ok if they will regret it. If they leave that company, I will sign them up quickly. Please know the facts before attacking me. Attack their company. Such great talent will be wasted if they don't get better support.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://seoulbeats.com/2011/05/so-teddy-and-rania-are-kaput-now-what/|title=So Teddy and Rania are now kaput. And now what?|work=Seoul Beats|date=26 May 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2011/05/teddy-riley-leaves-rania |title=Teddy Riley leaves Rania? |publisher=allkpop |date=2011-05-25 |accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref>\n\nThe group released their second EP, ''Time to Rock Da Show'', on November 16, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/2011/11/rania-releases-second-minbum-time-to-rock-da-show|title=RaNia releases second mini-album, \"Time To Rock Da Show\"|publisher=Allkpop.com|date=16 November 2011|accessdate=29 June 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://music.naver.com/album/index.nhn?albumId=300749|title=RaNia :: Time To Rock Da Show|work=Naver|date=16 November 2011|language=Korean}}</ref> The music video for its title track, \"Pop Pop Pop\", written by [[Brave Brothers]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/2011/10/rania-to-make-a-comeback-with-brave-brothers-this-year|title=Rania to make a comeback with Brave Brothers this year|publisher=Allkpop.com|date=23 October 2011|accessdate=29 June 2012}}</ref> was revealed four days later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/2011/11/rania-reveals-pop-pop-pop-mv |title=RaNia reveals \"Pop Pop Pop\" music video|publisher=Allkpop.com|date=20 November 2011}}</ref> Joy suddenly went on hiatus at this time, which DR Music claimed was because her parents' house had been affected in the flood which occurred in [[Thailand]] at the time of the release,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/7825/ranias-thai-member-joy-indefinitely-leaves-group-brother-still-missing-from-thai-floods|title=RaNia's Thai Member Joy Indefinitely Leaves Group; Brother Still Missing From Thai Floods|publisher=Mwave|date=12 June 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|language=Korean|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20120612n04112/|title=RaNia's agency explains Joys absence|date=12 June 2012}}</ref> and later left Rania in June 2012. In a series of now-deleted tweets, she wrote \"To everyone, I'm sorry I let you guys down so many times, but I\u2019ve been thinking about it for months. I think I can't go back to stand on that place anymore. [...] I can't go back anymore. Thanks for all of your love and all of your hope, thank you so much and I feel so sorry that I [am disappointing beloved fans]\u2026From now\u2026I think I can't be in the entertainment [industry] or back to be a singer anymore since I was sick\u2026But I haven't got any confidence to go back to do it. I'm sorry that I made you all have to wait for me\u2026and I made you all feel confused. Thank you so much for gifts, kindness, love that you give me. Thank you.\" <ref>{{cite web|url=https://wowkpop.wordpress.com/2012/04/04/has-joy-left-rania/ |title=Has Joy left Rania? &#124; wowkpop |publisher=Wowkpop.wordpress.com |date=2018-03-26 |accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref> On 30 May 2012, Rania performed a new song named \"Killer\" at the Dream Concert. They made a comeback on September 16 with second digital single \"Style\", whose music video was revealed on September 20. Jooyi did not participate in this comeback,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/15485/rania-to-return-as-five-members-with-new-single|title=RaNia to Return as Five Members With New Single|date=20 September 2012|website=Mwave}}</ref> although DR Music claimed she was still a member of the group.\n\n===2013\u20132014: Further releases, line-up changes and group hiatus===\n[[File:Rania at the Hyosung Angel Village Festival, 4 October 2013 03.jpg|thumb|right|Rania performing at the Hyosung Angel Village Festival, on October 4, 2013.]]\nRania released the lead single \"Just Go\" on March 8, 2013, along with their third mini album, also titled ''Just Go (Goodbye's The New Hello)''.<ref name=\"justgoriko\">{{cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/30945/rania-release-new-mv|title=[Video] RaNia Releases New MV and Explains Riko's Absence|date=8 March 2013|website=Mwave}}</ref> They also announced to debut in America in summer 2013.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2013/03/rania-to-start-promotions-in-the-u-s-during-the-summer|title=RaNia to start promotions in the US during the summer}}</ref> Empire Records was to be handling the girls' distribution while Fireworks was to handle their American management.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/18985/rania-signs-with-empire-records-to-begin-entry-into-american-music-market|title=RaNia Signs with Empire Records to Begin Entry into American Music Market|date=26 October 2012|website=Mwave}}</ref> Larry Rudolph and [[Adam Leber]], two of [[Britney Spears]]' managers, decided to be Rania's managers throughout their U.S. promotions.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2013/03/rania-to-team-up-with-britney-spears-managers-for-their-u-s-promotions|title=RaNia to team up with Britney Spears' managers for their U.S. promotions|date=28 March 2013}}</ref> Starting May 21, Rania began filming for their MTV reality show ''Road to Fame'' in [[Los Angeles]] and other cities across the U.S. The show would feature the group's preparations for their U.S. debut and would air for three months. It was also revealed that the album would feature collaborations with both [[Snoop Dogg]] and [[2 Chainz]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/32959/snoop-dogg-to-rap-for-rania|title=RaNia to Collaborate with Snoop Dogg and 2 Chainz|date=2 April 2013|website=Mwave}}</ref> However, Rania's American debut was delayed again in June.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2013/07/rania-plans-seven-country-promotional-tour-us-advancement-delay|title=RaNia plans seven country promotional tour + US advancement delay|date=8 July 2013}}</ref> Instead, they began to film a CF for Woongjin Waterpark Play\u00b0C<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2013/06/the-ladies-of-rania-embrace-the-warm-weather-in-their-sexy-woongjin-play-doci-cf-making-film|title=The ladies of RaNia embrace the warm weather in their sexy 'Woongjin Play Doci' CF + making film|date=12 June 2013}}</ref> and released a special digital single titled \"Up\" for fans on July 5.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2013/07/rania-splash-around-in-bikinis-for-up-mv|title=RaNia splash around in bikinis for \"Up\" MV + free song download|date=4 July 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2014, the group signed with Spanish label INGENIOmedia and confirmed they would have a comeback in July with \"Acceleration\", with a second round of promotions in September.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2014/05/rania-to-make-a-comeback-in-july-with-acceleration-spanish-intro-added-to-style-mv|title=RaNia to make a comeback in July with 'Acceleration' + Spanish intro added to 'Style' MV|date=3 May 2014}}</ref> The label also confirmed that they were looking for a sixth member to replace Riko, who was absent from the group since \"Just Go\".<ref name=\"justgoriko\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2014/05/rania-to-hold-an-audition-to-recruit-another-member|title=RaNia to hold an audition to recruit another member|date=5 May 2014}}</ref> Following an incident where a staffer at INGENIOmedia leaked Rania's comeback track to a [[sasaeng fan]], the company severed ties with the group, stating they were \"taking too long\".<ref>{{cite web|language=es|url=https://www.facebook.com/INGENIOmedia/posts/932342023447995|title=Question about Rania to INGENIOmedia|date=29 July 2014|website=[[Facebook]]}}</ref> INGENIOMedia later released a statement saying that they were not looking for a member to replace Riko, apologizing for any confusion, and said that any news on member changes would have to come from Rania's company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2014/05/rania-to-hold-an-audition-to-recruit-another-member |title=RaNia to hold an audition to recruit another member |publisher=allkpop |date=2014-05-05 |accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref>\n\nIn late 2014, Saem stopped attending public events and deactivated her official social media accounts. This led to intense fan speculation that she had left the group, but DR Music did not release an official statement regarding her situation. Soon afterwards, DR Music announced Riko's departure, releasing a statement saying: \"After the completion of the promotions of the single \"Style\", Riko told us with that she would take her university entrance exams to study a career, she asked for a three year break to complete her university studies and once she graduated from college, she could return to the group as a member of RaNia, but the problem came back this year when she reproached subjects in the university, she made us aware of this situation and asked for a year more absence that we found impossible since although she promotes or not with the group, we as a company should continue paying a normal salary, And That is unfair for us and the other members of the group, because she can not postpone her absence anymore, she decided to leave the group and the agency.\" DR Music later added a new member, Sharon Park, who was a model before joining the group.\n\n===2015\u20132016: Return with ''Demonstrate'' and line-up changes===\nIn January 2015, Jooyi stopped attending live performances with RaNia. When asked for an update on the situation, DR Music claimed that she was simply on hiatus. In April 2015, Sharon Park left the group to focus on her modeling career. In July 2015, the group made their appearance with two new members, trainees Seulji and Hyeme. In October 2015, they were announced to be having a comeback as a six-member group on November 6 with their third EP ''Demonstrate''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2015/10/rania-to-demonstrate-a-strong-return-after-2-year-hiatus |title=RaNia to 'Demonstrate' a strong return after 2-year hiatus |publisher=allkpop |date=2015-10-29 |accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref> On 3 November, Seulji and Hyeme were revealed as new members<ref name=SeuljiHyeme>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2015/11/rania-drop-a-ton-of-teaser-images-introduce-new-members |title=RaNia drop a ton of teaser images + introduce new members |publisher=allkpop |date=2015-11-03 |accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref> and it was announced that ''Demonstrate'' would feature African-American rapper Alexandra Reid, with the possibility of her becoming a new member of the group.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2015/11/rania-demonstrate-what-theyve-got-in-mv-teaser-ft-american-rapper-and-possibly-new-member |title=RaNia 'Demonstrate' what they've got in MV teaser ft. American rapper and possibly new member? |publisher=allkpop |date=2015-11-03 |accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref> On November 4, DR Music confirmed that [[Alexandra Reid]] had joined the group, while confirming Saem and Jooyi's departures.<ref name=Alex>{{cite news|language=Korean|url=http://www.xportsnews.com/jenter/?ac=article_view&entry_id=654544&_REFERER=http%3A%2F%2Fsearch.naver.com%2Fsearch.naver%3Fwhere%3Dnexearch%26query%3D%25EB%259D%25BC%25EB%258B%2588%25EC%2595%2584%26sm%3Dtop_hty%26fbm%3D1%26ie%3Dutf8|title=\ub77c\ub2c8\uc544, \u7f8e \ud751\uc778 \ub798\ud37c \uc54c\ub809\uc0b0\ub4dc\ub77c \ud569\ub958 '\ud654\ub824\ud55c \uc774\ub825'|date=4 November 2015}}</ref> Alex is the first African-American woman to be an official member of a South Korean girl group.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.koreaboo.com/news/rania-to-promote-with-first-ever-official-african-american-member-in-k-pop/|title=\nRaNia to promote with first ever official African American member in K-Pop|date=4 November 2015}}</ref>\n\nDR Music sent out a letter to fans that supported their Makestar project, informing them that RaNia's comeback had been pushed back to August 2016, and they were working on a Hyeme & Alex sub-unit instead. On July 13, 2016, however, Makestar announced that due to repeated failed attempts to contact DR Music about the project's progress and \"the continued irresponsible behavior and stance taken by the RaNia project creator, and our unwillingness to ignore the inconvenience this is causing to the project participants\", the project would be terminated and all money returned to the fans.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asianjunkie.com/2016/07/13/makestar-is-refunding-the-backers-of-ranias-project-so-they-are-literally-cancelled/ |title=Makestar is refunding the backers of RaNia's project, so they are literally cancelled \u2013 Asian Junkie |publisher=Asianjunkie.com |date=2016-07-13 |accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref> \n\nOn May 26, it was confirmed that the last three original members of RaNia - Di, T-ae and Xia had withdrawn from the group and parted ways from [[DR Music]] after five years. They then signed with their new label Enter Hama, where they announced their plans to redebute as \"Ela8te\", although these plans fell through.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/05/members-leave-rania-and-company-to-form-new-girl-group |title=Members leave RaNia and company to form new girl group? |publisher=allkpop |date=2016-05-26 |accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref> \n\nOn June 26, RaNia performed at a Chinese event with three DR Music trainees: Jian, Jieun (a former member of [[LPG (South Korean band)|LPG]]) and Crystal. On August 15, 2016, Alex announced that she was the group's new leader. On October 25, RaNia performed with two DR Music trainees (Ttabo and Hyeonji) at the 2016 Seoul ICARUS Drone International Film Festival. Two days later DR Music stated that from seven DR Music trainees they would choose new RaNia members.\n\n===2017: Reformation as BP RaNia and line-up changes===\nOn December 23, 2016, DR Music revealed a teaser image for \"BP RaNia\" (\"Black Pearl\" RaNia, in reference to Alex's darker skintone) and hinted a comeback as a seven-member group.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/12/rania-teases-for-comeback |title=RaNia teases for comeback |publisher=allkpop |date=2016-12-22 |accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref> On December 24, an image teaser for Hyeme and new member Jieun were revealed.<ref name=\"Jieun\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/12/rania-reveals-photos-of-two-new-members |title=RaNia reveals photos of two new members! |publisher=allkpop |date=2016-12-23 |accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref> On 25 December, Zi.U (formerly known as Seulji) and new member Yumin teaser images were revealed.<ref name=\"Zimin\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/12/rania-drop-teaser-images-for-ziu-and-youmin |title=RaNia drop teaser images for Zi.U and Youmin! |publisher=allkpop |date=2016-12-24 |accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref> On December 26, DR Music revealed teaser images for Alex and new Chinese member Ttabo.<ref name=\"bo\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/12/rania-drop-teaser-images-for-alex-and-new-member-ttabo |title=RaNia drop teaser images for Alex and new member Ttabo! |publisher=allkpop |date= |accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref> It was reported that former member Saem had rejoined the group after two years following her departure in late 2014, and that she had changed her stage name to Yina.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://weibo.com/u/5238387873?profile_ftype=1&is_all=1#_0 |title=Sina Visitor System |publisher=Weibo.com |date= |accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref><ref>https://scontent-iad3-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/15665608_1658503231115233_711628787665314403_n.jpg?oh=93649179b98b9e444a422197ccdcd78a&oe=58F696EF</ref> On December 27, DR Music revealed last teaser image for Saem, confirming that she had re-joined the group.<ref name=\"Yina\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/12/rania-introduces-the-final-member-of-group-before-comeback |title=RaNia introduces the final member of group before comeback |publisher=allkpop |date=2016-12-26 |accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref> On December 28, RaNia released their first teaser music video for their upcoming comeback track \"Start a Fire\" as BP RaNia.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.liveen.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=143920|title=\ub77c\uc774\ube0c\uc5d4|date=2017-01-20|access-date=2017-02-16|language=ko}}</ref> \"Start a Fire\" was released on December 30, 2016, along with their fourth EP of the same name.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.hankooki.com/m_dh_view.php?WM=dh&FILE_NO=ZGgyMDE2MTIyOTE5NDMyODEzOTA1MC5odG0=&ref=#_adtep |title=\ub77c\ub2c8\uc544, 7\uc778\uc870 \uc644\uc804\uccb4 \ucef4\ubc31...'BP\ub77c\ub2c8\uc544'\ub85c \ubcf8\uaca9 \ud65c\ub3d9 |publisher=M.hankooki.com |date= |accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref> DR Music said \"Through Spanish company INGENIOmedia, the song will be available in more than 60 countries around the world.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/930779wpp/watch-bp-rania-gets-ready-start-fire-revamped-group-comeback-mv|title=Watch: BP RANIA Gets Ready To \"Start A Fire\" With Revamped Group In Comeback MV|website=Soompi}}</ref> \n\nOn February 10 2017, DR Music announced that BP RaNia would start promotions for their second song \"Make Me Ah\" from the ''Start a Fire'' EP, on February 14.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=DRMUSIC_RANIA|author=BP Rania Official|number=830047458918948865|date=10 February 2017|title=2\uc6d4 \uc2a4\ucf00\uc904\uc774 \uc5c5\ub370\uc774\ud2b8 \ub418\uc5c8\uc2b5\ub2c8\ub2e4.  2\uc6d4 14\uc77c SBSMTV \ub354\uc1fc (Make Me Ah)}}</ref> It was also announced that this would be the first time that Alex would take part in the entire choreography.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/12/rania-start-a-fire-in-upcoming-mv-teaser-as-bp-rania |title=RaNia 'Start a Fire' in upcoming MV teaser as BP RaNia! |publisher=allkpop |date=2016-12-27 |accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref>\n\nOn February 21, DR Music revealed that the company was approached by a well established production company with an acting opportunity for Alex, to which they responded by releasing a statement saying that they hoped that fans could understand the benefits of this opportunity, and that the opportunity would \"allow the group to gain exposure and help BP RaNia's success by expanding their fan base.\" DR Music assured the fans that Alex would remain a fully active member of BP RaNia, and would return to her regular schedules after her return to Korea.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/drmusicrania/posts/701856799975543 |title=RANIA - \uc548\ub155\ud558\uc138\uc694 A1ST\uc5ec\ub7ec\ubd84 \uc54c\ub808\uc0b0\ub4dc\ub77c\uc758 \ud5a5\ud6c4 \uc2a4\ucf00\uc974\uc5d0 \uad00\ud55c \uacf5\uc9c0\uc0ac\ud56d\uc785\ub2c8\ub2e4. \ucd5c\uadfc \ucf00\uc774\ud31d... |publisher=Facebook |date= |accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref> The company asked people to send positivity to Alex and to wait patiently and enthusiastically for their return. \n\nOn February 28, RaNia released their first compilation album ''RaNia Legends'', comprising songs from \"Dr Feel Good\" to \"Start a Fire\". \n\nOn May 12, DR Music announced that they were looking for three to four new members to start BP RaNia W, a worldwide group that would promote alongside the current members of BP RaNia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/drmusicrania/posts/743610459133510 |title=RANIA - \uc548\ub155\ud558\uc138\uc694 \ub514\uc54c\ubba4\uc9c1\uc785\ub2c8\ub2e4. \uae08\uc77c Born Star Newyork\uc5d0\uc11c \uc62c\ub9b0 \uc624\ub514\uc158\uacf5\uc9c0\uc5d0... |publisher=Facebook |date= |accessdate=2018-12-13}}</ref> \n\nNear the end of March fans noticed that Yina was absent from group promotions, to which DR Music replied that Yina was busy with her own individual activities. On June 8, Yina announced in an Instagram post that she was leaving BP RaNia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2017/06/yina-announces-her-departure-from-bp-rania|title=Yina announces her departure from BP RaNia|website=allkpop}}</ref> The agency later confirmed that Yina had decided to focus on her acting career.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/995711wpp/bp-rania-announces-yina-will-not-take-part-next-comeback|title=BP Rania Announces Yina Will Not Take Part In Next Comeback|website=Soompi}}</ref> \n\nBP RaNia remained as a six-membered group, releasing their seventh EP ''Refresh 7th'' on August 12, with title track \"Beep Beep Beep\". Promotions became controversial when fans noticed that Alex had very few lines, and in fact spent the majority of performances standing off to the side while the other girls danced and sang.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asianjunkie.com/2017/08/07/bp-rania-perform-beep-beep-beep-which-has-alex-standing-in-the-corner/|title=BP Rania perform \"Beep Beep Beep\", which has Alex standing in the corner}}</ref> On August 19, DR Music announced that Alex had left the group, and that the group would continue promotions as five.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/drmusicrania/posts/796124980548724|title=RANIA|website=www.facebook.com}}</ref> Following her departure, Alex took to Twitter and criticized the company in regards to how she was treated and her departure, saying \"People think they can push you around, take advantage of you, manipulate you, violate you then throw you in the trash and walk. Dead wrong.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2017/08/alexandra-expresses-criticism-following-her-departure-from-bp-rania|title=Alexandra expresses criticism following her departure from BP RaNia|website=allkpop}}</ref> On September 13, it was announced that the group would be making a comeback with \"Breathe Heavy\" from their ''Refresh 7th'' EP.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://sports.donga.com/3/all/20170913/86299791/1 |title=Archived copy |access-date=September 13, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171222181939/http://sports.donga.com/3/all/20170913/86299791/1 |archive-date=December 22, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n=== 2018\u2013present: Comeback as RaNia and line-up changes ===\n\nIn January 2018, after fans noticed that Ttabo had missed several appearances with the group, DR Music issued a statement stating she was filming a movie in China.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2018/03/dr-music-says-once-again-that-ttabo-is-not-leaving-the-group|title=DR Music says once again that Ttabo is not leaving the group|website=allkpop}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2018/01/dr-music-addresses-rumors-of-ttabo-leaving-rania|title=DR Music addresses rumors of Ttabo leaving RaNia|website=allkpop}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2018/03/rania-fans-wonder-if-ttabo-is-leaving-the-group-after-all|title=RaNia fans wonder if Ttabo is leaving the group after all|website=allkpop}}</ref> On May 31, DR Music announced the departure of Yumin from the group due to her having \"recently been faced with circumstances that make it increasingly hard for her to follow the extremely demanding team schedule\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/drmusicrania/posts/940749782752909|title=RANIA|website=www.facebook.com}}</ref> It was also announced that the group would be having a comeback in June and releasing a \"Best Of\" album in August, but neither event occurred.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1177711wpp/rania-announces-yumins-departure-june-comeback|title=Rania Announces Yumin's Departure And June Comeback|website=Soompi}}</ref> On June 28, it was announced that a new member named Namfon had joined the group. She made her first appearance on RaNia's Malaysia tour.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/A1stCentral/posts/1890178351281052|title=A1st Central|website=www.facebook.com}}</ref> \n\nOn July 17, former member Yumin was announced to be marrying former [[Topp Dogg]] member P-Goon.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1201539wpp/former-toppdogg-member-p-goon-former-rania-member-yumin-get-married|title=Former ToppDogg Member P-Goon And Former Rania Member Yumin To Get Married|website=Soompi}}</ref> In February 2019, Yumin revealed that following the birth of their son, she and P-Goon had separated, and she was raising the baby herself.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=108&aid=0002759603 | title=&#91;\ub2e8\ub3c5&#93;\uc720\ubbfc \"p\uad70\uacfc \ud604\uc7ac \ubcc4\uac70 \uc0c1\ud0dc..\uc544\uc774 \ub0b4\uac00 \ud0a4\uc6b0\ub294 \uc911\"(\uc804\ubb38)}}</ref> \n\nOn November 7, when asked via SNS by fans if she was still a member Ttabo stated that she is a \u201cformer idol\u201d, and following the discovery that every remaining member of the group had removed \"RaNia\" from their social media accounts and that the company had unfollowed some of the members, rumours began to circulate that DR Music as a company had gone bankrupt and was unable to continue operations, resulting in an unofficial disbandment.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.kpopmap.com/ttabo-reported-to-have-left-rania-for-good/ | title=Ttabo Reported to Have Left RaNia for Good? \u2022 Kpopmap| date=2018-11-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2018/11/ttabo-left-rania | title=Ttabo left Rania|website=allkpop}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2019/02/rania-disbanding-members-missing-fanbases-confused | title=RaNia Disbanding? Members missing? Fanbases confused|website=allkpop}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.kpopmap.com/bizarre-rania-social-media-behavior-has-fans-talking-disbandment-disappearances/ | title=Bizarre RaNia Social Media Behavior Has Fans Talking Disbandment & Disappearances|website=KpopMap| date=February 13, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2019/02/rania-member-ziu-says-forget-me-not-ziu-in-farewell-message | title=Rania member ZiU says \"Forget me not\" ZiU in farewell message|website=allkpop}}</ref>\n\nOn August 18, 2019, RaNia announced via their official Instagram account that they would be performing in Romania from September 4\u20135 with three unconfirmed members. Fans began speculating that this meant Zi.U and Jieun had left the group.<ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/B1Utn0Unkkf/</ref> On August 28, the group's official YouTube account uploaded a video confirming the Romania performance as well as revealing the three new members as Seunghyun, Larissa, and ex-[[Stellar (group)|Stellar]] member Youngheun, as well as confirming departures of Jieun, Zi.U and Ttabo.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LWlgpuzWcHA</ref>\n\nOn January 25, 2020, Namfon was announced to have left the group, bringing the group's total number of former members to 14. It was also revealed that the group has had no further activities since the performance in Romania.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2020/01/namfon-departs-from-rania|title=Namfon Departs from Rania|website=Allkpop}}</ref> On February 18, Namfon spoke with a fansite and alleged that DR Music did not care about the group, and expressed her hopes that the other members would be able to leave as quickly as possible.<ref>https://www.allkpop.com/article/2020/02/former-rania-member-namfon-reveals-dr-music-do-not-care-about-rania</ref> In March, Larissa was revealed to have returned to her home country of Brazil, and fans noticed she had \"liked\" a fan comment on RaNia's official instagram that said the company \"should just let the group die in peace\", as well as liking several other comments with the same sentiment.<ref>https://www.allkpop.com/article/2020/03/ranias-larissa-likes-comment-that-says-the-group-should-die-in-peace</ref>\n\n==Members==\n\n===Current members===\n* Hyeme (\ud61c\ubbf8)<ref name=\"members\">{{cite web|url=http://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?where=nexearch&sm=tab_ppn&query=%EB%9D%BC%EB%8B%88%EC%95%84&os=184088&ie=utf8&key=PeopleService|title=\ub77c\ub2c8\uc544 \ud504\ub85c\ud544|publisher=Naver|language=ko}}</ref>\n* Youngheun\n* Seunghyun\n* Larissa\n\n===Former members===\n* Yijo (\uc774\uc870)\n* Joy (\uc870\uc774)\n* Riko (\ub9ac\ucf54)\n* Jooyi (\uc8fc\uc774)\n* Di (\ub514)\n* T-ae (\ud2f0\uc560)\n* Xia (\uc2dc\uc544)\n* Yina (\uc774\ub098), previously known as Saem (\uc0d8)\n* [[Alexandra Reid|Alexandra]] (\uc54c\ub809\uc0b0\ub4dc\ub77c)<ref name=\"members\"/>\n* Yumin (\uc720\ubbfc)\n* Ttabo\n* Zi.U (\uc9c0\uc720), previously known as Seulji (\uc2ac\uc9c0)\n* Jieun\n* Namfon\n\n===Timeline===\n<timeline>\nImageSize   = width:650 height:250\nPlotArea    = width:475 height:225 left:75 bottom:20\nAlignbars   = justify\nDateFormat  = mm/dd/yyyy\nPeriod   = from:04/06/2011 till:12/31/2020\nTimeAxis = orientation:horizontal format:yyyy\n\nColors =\n id:a value:rgb(1,0,0) legend:FirstGeneration\n id:b value:rgb(1,0.5,0) legend:SecondGeneration\n id:c value:rgb(1,1,0) legend:ThirdGeneration\n id:d value:rgb(0,1,0) legend:FourthGeneration\n id:e value:rgb(0,0,1) legend:FifthGeneration\n id:f value:rgb(1,0,1) legend:SixthGeneration\n\nLegend = orientation:horizontal position:bottom\nScaleMajor = unit:year increment:1 start:2012 gridcolor:black\n\nPlotData =\n color:a width:7 textcolor:black align:left anchor:from\n bar:Yijo         from:start      till:04/30/2011\n bar:Joy          from:start      till:06/12/2012\n bar:Riko         from:start      till:03/08/2013\n bar:Jooyi        from:start      till:01/15/2015\n bar:Di             from:start      till:05/26/2016\n bar:T-ae         from:start      till:05/26/2016\n bar:Xia          from:start      till:05/26/2016\n bar:Yina         from:start      till:05/12/2014\n bar:Yina         from:12/27/2016 till:06/08/2017\n color:b width:7 textcolor:black align:left anchor:from\n bar:Alex         from:11/03/2015 till:08/19/2017\n bar:Zi.U         from: